# Documentation — read and maintain

## Before changing routes or user-visible behaviour

1. Skim [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) doc map.
2. Read [development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) if the change is a new feature (phases 1–4 before code).
3. Update the **lowest complexity** doc that covers the feature.

## After changes — update when relevant

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New domain term or invariant | [domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md) |
| New/changed UI route or menu | [feature-catalog.md](../../docs/feature-catalog.md), [application-guidelines.md](../../docs/application-guidelines.md) |
| Schema, entity, or shipped feature | [`dev-import.sql`](../../src/main/resources/dev-import.sql); [dev-import-sql-safety.mdc](dev-import-sql-safety.mdc); feature-catalog § Dev personas |
| HTMX event or auth refresh pattern | [htmx-events.md](../../docs/htmx-events.md) |
| CDI event producer/observer | [cdi-events.md](../../docs/cdi-events.md) |
| Package, URL map, patterns | [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) |
| Transversal technical decision | [docs/adr/](../../docs/adr/) — new or superseding ADR |
| Feature workflow narrative | `feature/<slug>.md` changelog |
| Doc debt closed | [conventions-checklist.md](../../docs/conventions-checklist.md) |
| User-facing capability bullet | [README.md](../../README.md) — [readme.mdc](readme.mdc) |
| UI class or token | [ui-elements.md](../../docs/ui-elements.md), [ui-palette.md](../../docs/ui-palette.md) |
| UX narrative for new page type | [ui-guidelines.md](../../docs/ui-guidelines.md) |

## Complexity order

1. **domain-specification** — vocabulary and rules
2. **feature/** changelog + **feature-catalog** — routes and click paths
3. **htmx-events** / **application-guidelines** — interaction flows
4. **ARCHITECTURE** — technical structure
5. **README** — pitch and links

## Quality bar

- No stale type names after renames — grep docs when renaming.
- Cross-link; avoid duplicating ADR rationale in ARCHITECTURE.md — link instead.

